1) We got request from respected team and mount point name with LUN.

2) open Hmc console and find repected Lpar.

3) Open Lpar go inside that in storage 

4) Click on LPAR name and then click on connection report it will show you storage if not then storage not assign yet

5) Take cli session of that LPAR/KVM/Vm.

6) ip r       ---confirm the Ip of server

7) multipath -ll

8) multipath -ll | grep -i 49A  ---check that LUN Id visibal or not (49A) last digit of LUN

9) df -hT     ---Check Mount point is existed in my case (DRNEO-MZP-EDB02 10.16.45.48 and I have to increase /pgsql-data-shared mount point)

10) cat /etc/multipath.conf | grep -i shared  --- It will show you Shared has attched Dsk attached, like (EDBDATASHARED-DISK2)

11) Go to Hmc and add Disk with next number (EDBDATASHARED-DISK3)

12) Take Cli session of that vm and backup of multipath.conf file cp /etc/multipath.conf /tmp  (or in swdump)

13) rescan-scsi-bus.sh   --- It will scan storage and showing you newly assign storage.

14) vi /etc/multipath.conf  --- Here add that LUN and name EDBDATASHARED-DISK3        ORABIN-DISK0
 
15) systemctl restart multipathd.service  --- It will restart the service and you can see the changes

16) rescan-scsi-bus.sh  ---Now that disk is visible with name
 
17) multipath -ll | grep -i shared  --- (shared is my mount pointname and I used Lun attached Disk with sahre name )

18) pvcreate -f /dev/mapper/EDBDATASHARED-DISK3
 
19) vgs  --- Here you can see the name of vg for refrence like (EDBDATASHAREDVG)
   
20) vgextend EDBDATASHAREDVG /dev/mapper/EDBDATASHARED-DISK3
  
21) df -hT

22) lvs

23) lvextend -l +100%FREE /dev/mapper/EDBDATASHAREDVG-EDBDATASHAREDLV

24) xfs_growfs /dev/mapper/EDBDATASHAREDVG-EDBDATASHAREDLV
  
25) df -hT  --- /pgsql-data-shared mount point has been increased
